In a large bowl, toss together the lettuce and tomatoes. Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Cook turkey in oil 6 to 8 minutes, turning occasionally, until no longer pink in center. Arrange turkey on lettuce mixture. Cook bacon in same skillet over low heat 8 to 10 minutes, turning occasionally, until crisp and brown. Drain bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons fat in skillet. Crumble bacon; sprinkle over salad. Cook onion in bacon fat about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender. Stir in sugar, mustard, pepper and vinegar. Cook about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally, until hot. Pour onion mixture over salad; toss. Top with croutons and cheese. Serve warm.